HEADWORD: Shellbark
<hw>Shell"bark`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A species of hickory (<spn>Carya alba</spn>) whose outer bark is
loose and peeling; a shagbark; also, its nut.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shelled</ent>⟦br⟧
